description.p:
Accordingly, the present invention provides a way to produce polymer modified bituminous binder compositions for road/paving applications without the necessity of adding crosslinking agents thereby greatly decreasing many of the environmental and safety concerns associated with the use of such crosslinking agents while at the same time maintaining or improving the properties of the compositions. More specifically, the present invention provides a process for preparing a polymer modified bituminous binder composition wherein the amount of crosslinking agent is less than 0.01% of the total weight of the polymer modified bituminous binder composition, said process comprising the steps of:
a. heating a bitumen component in a stirred tank to a temperature from about 185°C to about 221 °C;
b. adding from 2 to 36% by weight, based on the weight of the polymer modified bituminous binder composition of a block copolymer composition to the bitumen component while stirring the bitumen component to form a homogeneous mixture of the bitumen component and the block copolymer composition; or
a. heating a bitumen component in a stirred tank until it reaches a molten state;
b. adding from 2 to 36% by weight, based on the weight of the polymer modified bituminous binder composition of a block copolymer composition to the bitumen component and raising the temperature of the bitumen component and block copolymer composition to from 185°C to 221°C while stirring the bitumen component and block copolymer composition in order to form a homogeneous mixture of the bitumen component and the block copolymer composition;
and
c. continuing to stir the homogeneous mixture while maintaining the temperature from 185°C to 221°C for a period of time from about 4 hours to about 30 hours until a cured polymer modified bituminous binder composition is obtained;
wherein said block copolymer composition comprises
(i) 100% of a diblock copolymer comprising one block of a monovinylaromatic hydrocarbon and one block of a conjugated diene having a peak molecular weight from 30,000 to 78,000 and a vinyl content from 35 to 80 mol percent based on the number of repeat monomer units in the conjugated diene block, or a mixture of the diblock copolymer and
(ii) optionally one or more block copolymers comprising at least two blocks of monovinylaromatic hydrocarbon and at least one block of conjugated diene, the block copolymer selected from linear triblock copolymers, multiarm coupled block copolymers, and mixtures thereof, the linear triblock copolymers having a peak molecular weight that is 1.5 to 3.0 times the peak molecular weight of the diblock copolymer and multiarm coupled block copolymers having a peak molecular weight that is 1.5 to 9.0 times the peak molecular weight of the diblock copolymer, and each having a vinyl content from 35 to 80 mol percent based on the number of repeat monomer units in the conjugated diene block, wherein the peak molecular weight of each monovinyl aromatic hydrocarbon block in (i) and (ii) is from 10,000 to 25,000, and wherein the ratio of (i) to (ii) is greater than 1:1.
